stylometry: Sensitivity analysis allows you to use different inputs and see the difference of the outputs based on the different values of inputs you inserted.  For instance you could use sensitivity analysis to see the difference in the profit you would make based on the level of marketing costs incurred by the company.  This can go over a broad range so you are able to make better decisions.  It allows you to change the inputs and if they changes had any affect on the outputs from the previous input.  It is important because it gives businesses and companies the capability of see a variation based on the inputs and outputs where otherwise they would have had to do physically.  This allows them to save time and try and run a more accurate operation.
